args: Ya know, a guy can't help but wonder—\nis it still technically a ＂nap＂ if yer THAT\ndead to the world?
Aren't the Twelve Wyrmclan leaders\nsupposed to be, like, the cream of\nthe Hinomoto crop?
Was it truly wise to show her in simply\nbecause she asserted that this would\nmake an ＂excellent napping spot＂?
As long as she's comfortable,\nI suppose it's fine.
Zzz...zzzzz... Oh, bed...\nYou've always been there for me...
She's got a point—it's PERFECT napping\nweather! Get your sleep on, girl!
All right, throw up your dukes!
Yachiyo?! I thought you were out hunting\nfiends!
I was, but when I caught wind that one'a\nthe leaders of the Twelve Wyrmclans blew\ninto town, I made like a banana and split!

Talk about being committed to the cause!
Still, Mitsuhide's kind of a big deal in
Hinomoto. I'm not sure she'd accept a
challenge like—
Hah! Come on then, let's dance!
Wait, you're gonna duel NOW?\nWhat the heck is going on?!
...Perhaps it is just my imagination,\nbut the number of slumbering bodies\naround the castle seems to be on the rise.
Even Yachiyo, hm? For her to be here\nrather than dashing about making brazen\nchallenges is unusual indeed.
*yawn* Nah, actually, this IS a duel.
So, Yachiyo challenged Mitsuhide to a\nduel, right?
Hold up, time out, time out. You sure you\nshould duel with that blade? It's pretty\nnicked, isn't it?
Well I'll be! Must'a happened when I\nwas boppin' those fiends...
But you needn't worry! A nick or two won't\nimpede my performance in the slightest!
Seriously? Bit of a shame to use a\ndamaged weapon in a duel you\nwant to win, huh?
Don't you want us to go at each other with\neverything we've got?
W-well, when you put it that way...
I'm not going to run or hide.\nGo sharpen your blade.
And in the meantime...how about we\nhave a duel by MY rules?
So, they're dueling to see who can nap\nthe longest...?
A-yuuup. Oh, but I'm not dueling. I just got\nswept up in the sleepy mood and figured\nI'd catch a few winks. *yawn*
Mm... Oh, confound it.\nEver the early bird...
All right, Mitsuhide, let's take this\nfrom the top!
*yawn* Sure thing. Come at me...\nas many times...as you want...
This is absurd. Mitsuhide, surely you have\nmore important pursuits than sleeping your\nlife away?
Forgive my impertinence, but I think you\ngo too far in your pursuit of ＂chilling out＂—
How about you chill out a bit\nyourself, Cleo?
...Did you hear a word I just said?
You're always so serious. I've been\nwishing we could talk more casually.
You were fussing over me 'cause I'm an\nhonored guest from a foreign land, right?
Wouldn't it be nice to put all the\nformalities aside and just talk,\ngirl to girl?

I really think fostering a mutual
understanding between nations is key
to establishing good relations.
You feel me?
Very well. Your words hold merit.\nAs long as we don't tarry too long,\nI will join you.
Grrrrreat. Time for some group chilling!
After all, there are some things you just\ncan't talk about if you're stuck being\nstiff and formal...
Hey, there you are,\n{player_name}! Is it dinnertime?
Just about. We were a bit late getting back\nfrom fiend hunting. Sorry about that.
*sigh* Well, aren't you a model prince,\nalways breaking his back for the sake of\nthe people.
Why do you go to so much effort?
Why? I should think it's obvious.\nTo take care of my people and my friends.
A real Charitable Charles, aren't you?\nStill, I dunno, don't you ever feel like...
Like YOU don't even factor into the\nequation? Doesn't that feel empty?
Meh, we'll just leave it at that.\nAnyway, this kingdom's nice.
Things in the surrounding area are a little\ndicey, but all the people you've rallied\nhere seem like good-hearted folks.
Your castle's comfortable, the food's\nfour-star, and most importantly, the beds\nare a premier gateway to slumberland.
Well, I'm glad you find the kingdom\nto your liking.
I don't just like it—I love it.\nSo, how about you give it to me?
I mean, I think it'd be best for everyone\nif I ran things around here, yeah?
Hate to break it to ya,\n{player_name}, but we're with\nMitsuhide on this one.
What?! What's going on here, Mitsuhide?!
Oh, you know. Your allies are just plotting\nan uprising with me.
